]
description: """\
A formally verified algorithm for checking the acyclicity of a graph while
incrementally adding new edges and vertices to the graph.

This particular algorithm is optimized for the case of sparse graphs.

The (amortized) complexity of m arc insertions and n vertex insertions is
O(m min(m^(1/2), n^(2/3)) + n), i.e.:
- O(m sqrt(m) + n) for sparse graphs;
- O(m n^(2/3) + n) for dense graphs.

(See the companion paper for more details.)
"""
